tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The results show a mildly elevated hemoglobin and a markedly high platelet distribution width, with all other parameters within normal limits. These findings may reflect mild hemoconcentration or individual variation; the high platelet distribution width could indicate increased platelet size variability, possibly due to platelet activation or turnover. Correlation with clinical context is recommended.
